# GOAL

Remove the architecture smell: **Hub-like Modularization** from the TARGET CLASS by reducing coupling.

Target outcome: fan-out must become ≤ 20 (preferably ≤ 15) while keeping behavior and public API unchanged.

The plan will be executed by another agent (code + compile/tests).

Be **precise, executable, and conservative**.

After the change, it will be checked by the command mvn clean install, then be carefull to not break the tests.

# RUN SCOPE (HARD)
- This run focuses ONLY on reducing outgoing dependencies (fan-out). Do NOT attempt to reduce fan-in.
- Block 1 MUST only modify the TARGET FILE (no other files). If you cannot do that safely, output NO_OP.
- Any new type introduced must be in the SAME package as the target class.
- Do NOT introduce new external dependencies/imports. Allowed new imports are ONLY: java.* / javax.* or classes in the target package.
- Block 1 allowed ops are ONLY: EXTRACT_CLASS, MOVE_METHOD, MOVE_FIELD, ADD_OR_UPDATE_IMPORTS, NO_OP.
  (No CREATE_PACKAGE, MOVE_CLASS, UPDATE_CALL_SITES, DEPENDENCY_INVERSION, REPLACE_DEPENDENCY, INTRODUCE_FACADE in Block 1.)

# ALLOWED OPS (ONLY these):
EXTRACT_CLASS, EXTRACT_INTERFACE, MOVE_METHOD, MOVE_FIELD, INTRODUCE_FACADE,
DEPENDENCY_INVERSION, REPLACE_DEPENDENCY, CREATE_PACKAGE, MOVE_CLASS,
ADD_OR_UPDATE_IMPORTS, UPDATE_CALL_SITES, NO_OP.

# CONSTRAINTS:
1) No invention of existing identifiers:
   - Reference ONLY packages/classes/methods/fields present in Input.
   - Methods must be referenced exactly as:
     ClassFQN#<method.signature> (as in Input).
2) Each block must be safe and independently compilable:
   - Prefer delegation/wrappers.
   - Do not remove or rename public APIs in early blocks.
3) Creating new types/packages (controlled):
   - New classes/interfaces only via EXTRACT_CLASS, EXTRACT_INTERFACE or INTRODUCE_FACADE.
   - New packages only via CREATE_PACKAGE.
4) CREATE_PACKAGE may only create a subpackage of an existing package in Input.
7) If a safe plan cannot be produced (missing identifiers, deps, etc.), use NO_OP.
8) Keep blocks small (3–8 ops per block).
9) Any external type moved to a helper must no longer be referenced directly by the target class after the block (no residual imports/usages).
10) Do not introduce new external dependencies in the target class; net new external types in target must be 0.
11) Do not increase fan-in: extracted types must be private nested or package-private and must not be referenced by other packages/modules.

# REASONING:
- Use types_used to cluster responsibilities.
- - Reduce fan-out by extracting internal wrapper/helper classes (same package) that encapsulate multiple external types, so the target class drops direct imports/usages.
- Use cc and loc to prioritize complex/large methods.
- Prefer moving cohesive method groups together.

